President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8 pm on Monday, February 1, 2021, on developments in relation to the country’s response to the Coronavirus pandemic. The address follows meetings in recent days of the National Coronavirus Command Council (NCCC), the President’s Coordinating Council (PCC) and Cabinet. The President’s address will be broadcast and streamed on a range of platforms that are accessible to South Africans and international audiences. 